---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead
		title={`Rating Methodology — How We Rate AI Tools | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
		description="Learn how AI Briefs evaluates and rates AI tools. Our transparent scoring system covers ease of use, value for money, features, reliability, and more."
	/>
</head>
<body>
<Header />

<section class="page-header">
	<div class="container">
		<Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Rating Methodology' }]} />
		<h1>How We Rate AI Tools</h1>
		<p>Our evaluation process is independent, transparent, and hands-on. Here's exactly how we score every tool in our directory.</p>
	</div>
</section>

<main class="container method-body">

	<section class="intro-block">
		<p>Every AI tool listed on {SITE_TITLE} that carries a star rating has been assessed by our editorial team against a defined set of criteria. We aim to give you an honest, balanced view — not a sponsored ranking. Tools that pay for listing receive no scoring advantage.</p>
		<p>Our scores reflect the experience of a typical non-technical user exploring an AI tool for the first time, as well as the expectations of power users and professionals where applicable.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Score Criteria -->
	<section class="criteria-section">
		<h2>Scoring Criteria</h2>
		<p>Each tool is rated out of <strong>5.0</strong>, calculated as a weighted average of five core dimensions:</p>

		<div class="criteria-grid">
			<div class="criterion">
				<div class="crit-header">
					<span class="crit-icon">🎯</span>
					<div>
						<h3>Ease of Use</h3>
						<span class="crit-weight">25% weight</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>How quickly can a new user get value from the tool? We assess onboarding, UI clarity, prompt guidance, and learning curve. A tool that delivers results within minutes scores higher than one requiring extensive configuration.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="criterion">
				<div class="crit-header">
					<span class="crit-icon">⚡</span>
					<div>
						<h3>Output Quality</h3>
						<span class="crit-weight">30% weight</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>The most important factor. We test the tool across a range of representative tasks and evaluate the accuracy, creativity, coherence, and usefulness of the results. We compare outputs against competing tools in the same category.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="criterion">
				<div class="crit-header">
					<span class="crit-icon">💰</span>
					<div>
						<h3>Value for Money</h3>
						<span class="crit-weight">20% weight</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>We assess whether the tool's pricing is fair relative to what it delivers. Free tiers, usage limits, hidden paywalls, and the generosity of trial periods all factor into this score. A generous free tier can significantly boost this dimension.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="criterion">
				<div class="crit-header">
					<span class="crit-icon">🔧</span>
					<div>
						<h3>Features & Depth</h3>
						<span class="crit-weight">15% weight</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>Does the tool do what it claims, and does it go beyond the basics? We evaluate the breadth of capabilities, integrations, API access, customisation options, and unique features that differentiate it from the crowd.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="criterion">
				<div class="crit-header">
					<span class="crit-icon">🛡️</span>
					<div>
						<h3>Reliability & Trust</h3>
						<span class="crit-weight">10% weight</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>We assess uptime, response speed, data privacy practices, and how transparent the company is about how its AI works. Tools with clear privacy policies, a known team, and a solid track record score higher here.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Star Scale -->
	<section class="scale-section">
		<h2>What the Stars Mean</h2>
		<div class="star-scale">
			<div class="star-row star-5">
				<span class="stars">★★★★★</span>
				<div>
					<strong>5.0 — Exceptional</strong>
					<p>Best-in-class. Leads its category in output quality, ease of use, and value. Recommended without reservation.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="star-row star-4">
				<span class="stars">★★★★☆</span>
				<div>
					<strong>4.0–4.9 — Very Good</strong>
					<p>Strong performer with minor gaps. Excellent for most users and use cases.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="star-row star-3">
				<span class="stars">★★★☆☆</span>
				<div>
					<strong>3.0–3.9 — Good</strong>
					<p>Solid tool with notable limitations. Useful for specific needs but may not be the first choice.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="star-row star-2">
				<span class="stars">★★☆☆☆</span>
				<div>
					<strong>2.0–2.9 — Below Average</strong>
					<p>Has potential but falls short in key areas. Consider alternatives before committing.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="star-row star-1">
				<span class="stars">★☆☆☆☆</span>
				<div>
					<strong>1.0–1.9 — Poor</strong>
					<p>Significant issues with quality, reliability, or pricing. Not recommended at this time.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Process -->
	<section class="process-section">
		<h2>Our Review Process</h2>
		<div class="process-steps">
			<div class="step">
				<span class="step-num">1</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Discovery</h3>
					<p>We identify tools through submissions, product launches, community feedback, and our own research. Every tool is checked against our listing criteria before evaluation begins.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="step">
				<span class="step-num">2</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Hands-On Testing</h3>
					<p>Our team creates a free or trial account and tests the tool across a standardised set of tasks relevant to its category. We do not rely on vendor-supplied demos or cherry-picked examples.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="step">
				<span class="step-num">3</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Scoring</h3>
					<p>Each reviewer independently scores the five criteria. Scores are combined into a weighted average, rounded to one decimal place, and reviewed against peer tools to ensure consistency.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="step">
				<span class="step-num">4</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Publication & Updates</h3>
					<p>Ratings are published alongside our review notes. We revisit ratings when a tool releases major updates, changes its pricing, or receives significant user feedback that warrants re-evaluation.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Independence notice -->
	<section class="notice-section">
		<div class="notice-card">
			<h2>Independence & Conflicts of Interest</h2>
			<p>{SITE_TITLE} earns revenue through sponsored listings and affiliate partnerships. However, our editorial ratings are strictly independent. Sponsored tools are labelled as such and receive no scoring advantage. Our team does not accept payment in exchange for higher ratings.</p>
			<p>If you believe a rating is inaccurate or outdated, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we will review it promptly.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

</main>

<Footer />
</body>
</html>

<style>
.page-header {
	background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-light) 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
}
.page-header h1 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem); margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
.page-header p { color: rgb(var(--gray)); max-width: 560px; }

.method-body { max-width: 820px; padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem; }

.intro-block {
	border-left: 3px solid var(--primary);
	padding-left: 1.25rem;
	margin-bottom: 3rem;
}
.intro-block p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

.criteria-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.criteria-section h2,
.scale-section h2,
.process-section h2,
.notice-section h2 {
	font-size: 1.3rem;
	margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.criteria-section > p { font-size: 0.93rem; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

.criteria-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }

.criterion {
	padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
	background: var(--bg);
}
.crit-header {
	display: flex;
	align-items: flex-start;
	gap: 0.85rem;
	margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
}
.crit-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.1rem; }
.crit-header h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin: 0 0 0.15rem; }
.crit-weight { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); background: var(--primary-light); padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 99px; }
.criterion p { font-size: 0.87rem; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin: 0; }

.scale-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.star-scale { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
.star-row {
	display: flex;
	align-items: flex-start;
	gap: 1rem;
	padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
	background: var(--bg);
}
.stars { font-size: 1.1rem; flex-shrink: 0; min-width: 90px; margin-top: 0.1rem; }
.star-5 .stars { color: #16a34a; }
.star-4 .stars { color: #22c55e; }
.star-3 .stars { color: #f59e0b; }
.star-2 .stars { color: #f97316; }
.star-1 .stars { color: #ef4444; }
.star-row strong { font-size: 0.95rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
.star-row p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin: 0; }

.process-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.process-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
.step {
	display: flex;
	align-items: flex-start;
	gap: 1.25rem;
	padding: 1.25rem;
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
}
.step-num {
	width: 36px;
	height: 36px;
	background: var(--primary);
	color: #fff;
	border-radius: 50%;
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	justify-content: center;
	font-weight: 800;
	font-size: 0.95rem;
	flex-shrink: 0;
}
.step h3 { font-size: 0.97rem; margin: 0 0 0.35rem; }
.step p { font-size: 0.87rem; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin: 0; line-height: 1.65; }

.notice-card {
	background: var(--primary-light);
	border: 1px solid rgba(0,200,150,0.3);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
	padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
}
.notice-card h2 { border: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }
.notice-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(var(--gray-dark)); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
.notice-card a { color: var(--primary); font-weight: 600; }
.notice-card a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
